            <title>[CXF-6444] CrossOriginResourceSharingFilter.java should not set Origin=* when Credentials=true</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6444</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to this: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/cors/#resource-preflight-requests&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/cors/#resource-preflight-requests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...when Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true is set, the response Origin: must be the same as the request Origin (see bullet #7).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t say why in the RFC (that I could see), but I presume there are security implications.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
